This is only to make management and uploading of SSIS packages easier for the DBA who is responsible for managing it.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
When you create any connections like a SQL job for instance, it will still have to reference the server where the msdb is located instead of the server where you added the XML entries.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
One way to view this XML configuration is to see it as a &quot;central Management Server&quot; for SSIS packages, just a central point of management.

